history.content:
Fairly do-able. I thought 161 was one of the easier upper div's I took and even (potentially unpopular opinion) lighter than 188. 

I think you'll find that the balance between the two classes is more skewed towards 162 (of course depending on how efficiently your group operates) but I would say if you felt comfortable with your workload last semester, you can expect a slightly harder workload this semester.

children.subject:
Hmm it's definitely possible this can happen since the sites for this semester are not up yet but looking at last semester's websites it seems they actually stagger for the most part (using the due dates for the code and not the final report).

https://cs162.eecs.berkeley.edu/

http://www-inst.cs.berkeley.edu/~cs161/fa16/#Projects

Even considering this, though, I think you will find a similar workload in most classes that have projects when paired with 162 just because 162 is, by nature, a fairly heavy course. You are building features into a working OS, after all.

I remember hearing from someone last semester that those two together is a bad combo simply because project deadlines coincide. I'm not sure if this is 100% true because I heard this from someone else.
